sentences: Chester Burton "Chet" Atkins (June 20, 1924 – June 30, 2001), known as "Mr. Guitar"  and "The Country Gentleman", was an American musician, occasional vocalist, songwriter, and record producer who, along with Owen Bradley and Bob Ferguson, helped create the Nashville sound, the country music style which expanded its appeal to adult pop music fans.
He also received nine Country Music Association awards for Instrumentalist of the Year.
Atkins was born on June 20, 1924, in Luttrell, Tennessee, near Clinch Mountain.
